radiographic_examinations.findings: Relative lucency of a portion of the right lower lobe centrally, which may represent congenital lobar emphysema. No pleural or pericardial effusion. Appendix is dilated and fluid filled, with mucosal hyperemia, and surrounding fat stranding. No evidence of drainable fluid collection or extraluminal air. Small amount of free fluid in the pelvis. A tiny umbilical hernia containing fat is noted. No evidence of focal lesions in liver, pancreas, spleen, or kidneys. No abdominal aortic aneurysm.
